import React, { useState } from "react"; import { Card, CardContent, CardDescription, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "./card"; import { Button } from "./button"; import { Badge } from "./badge"; import { Input } from "./input"; export function DietCompatibilityChecker() { const [selectedDiet, setSelectedDiet] = useState(""); const [restrictions, setRestrictions] = useState([]); const [allergies, setAllergies] = useState([]); const [budget, setBudget] = useState(""); const dietTypes = [ { name: "Keto", icon: "🥑", description: "High-fat, low-carb" }, { name: "Vegan", icon: "🌱", description: "Plant-based only" }, { name: "Mediterranean", icon: "🫒", description: "Heart-healthy" }, { name: "Paleo", icon: "🥩", description: "Ancient human diet" }, { name: "DASH", icon: "❤️", description: "Blood pressure control" }, { name: "Intermittent Fasting", icon: "⏰", description: "Time-restricted eating" } ]; const commonRestrictions = [ "Gluten-free", "Dairy-free", "Nut-free", "Soy-free", "Egg-free", "Seafood-free" ]; const commonAllergies = [ "Peanuts", "Tree nuts", "Milk", "Eggs", "Soy", "Wheat", "Fish", "Shellfish" ]; const budgetRanges = [ { range: "₹3,000", label: "Student Budget" }, { range: "₹8,000", label: "Family Budget" }, { range: "₹15,000", label: "Premium Lifestyle" } ]; const [showResults, setShowResults] = useState(false); const handleRestrictionToggle = (restriction) => { setRestrictions(prev => prev.includes(restriction) ? prev.filter(r => r !== restriction) : [...prev, restriction] ); }; const handleAllergyToggle = (allergy) => { setAllergies(prev => prev.includes(allergy) ? prev.filter(a => a !== allergy) : [...prev, allergy] ); }; const handleCheckCompatibility = () => { setShowResults(true); }; return (
